We study the problem of (approximate) maximin share
(MMS) allocation of indivisible items among a set of agents.
We focus on the graphical valuation model, in which the 
input is given by a graph where edges correspond to items, 
and vertices correspond to agents. An edge may have 
non-zero marginal value only for its incident vertices. We 
study additive, XOS and subadditive valuations and we 
present positive and negative results for (approximate) 
MMS fairness, and also for (approximate) pair-wise 
maximin share (PMMS) fairness.